## Completed Phase 6 of the Project [Development Plan](./.ai/guidelines/development-plan.md).

### Code Updates
1) The monolithic `./resources/js/types/page-props.ts` removed and page prop contracts now live in:
        - [shared.ts](./resources/js/types/admin/shared.ts)
        - [dashboard.ts](./resources/js/types/admin/dashboard.ts)
        - [users.ts](./resources/js/types/admin/users.ts)
        - [roles.ts](./resources/js/types/admin/roles.ts)
        - [permissions.ts](./resources/js/types/admin/permissions.ts)
        - [settings.ts](./resources/js/types/settings.ts).
2) Admin pages, settings pages, and the affected admin composables/components now import those slice-local types instead of the old shared dump. The auth shared prop typing was also refined in [auth.ts](./resources/js/types/auth.ts).
3) The backend DTOs that drive those page payloads now implement the `#[TypeScript]` attribute across the auth, shared, users, roles and permissions slices.
4) Pest enforces both halves of the contract drift fix in [BackendArchitectureContractsTest.php](./tests/Unit/BackendArchitectureContractsTest.php). The frontend-bound DTO/request classes must stay marked for TS generation, and the old monolithic page-prop file must stay dead.
5) Frontend build failure due to `Record<string, never>` in Vue SFC props was fixed by replacing with a plain empty props type.


### Tests and Validations Run and Passed
- `php artisan boost:update --ansi`
- `composer run style:fix`
- `composer run phpstan`
- `composer run rector`
- `composer run test:type-coverage`
- `composer run test:parallel`
- `npm run test:frontend`
- `npm run build`
